04/Jun/06 11:45 AM;557058:04670d95-8ea4-4705-9d43-683a4fdf2d81;From Ursula  (u.raab at worldonline.de) Thursday, 3 July 2003, 12:35 AM:

I wrote a function which can be called in text-to_html instead of nl2br. This function changes only the returns which are not enclosed by <pre> and </pre>

This is my function:



function nl2br_not_formatted ($text){

// this function replaces all returns to <br /> which are not enclosed by <pre> and </pre>

// so preformatted text is not altered

    $pos=0;

    $len=strlen($text);

    $new_text=;

    // convert returns to <br /> if text is not preformatted

    while ($pos<$len-1) {

      $pre_pos=strpos ($text, <pre>,$pos);// find position of next pre tag

      if (!$pre_pos) {

        $pre_pos=$len-1;

      }

      $new_text=$new_text . nl2br (substr ($text, $pos, $pre_pos));

      $pos=$pre_pos;

      $pre_pos=strpos ($text, </pre>,$pos);// find position of next /pre tag

      if (!$pre_pos) {

 $pre_pos=$len-1;

      } else {

  $pre_pos+=6;

      }

      $new_text=$new_text .substr($text, $pos, $pre_pos);

      $pos=$pre_pos;

    }

    return $new_text;

}



